description:
This Environmental Product Declaration (EPD) report pertains to a market average mix of solution and beck dyed
           AtlasMasland styrene butadiene latex backed broadloom carpet. All broadloom carpets made by AtlasMasland are
           included in this study. This is an EPD report to account for improvements to the carpet architecture and a continuing
           update of products after the merger of Atlas and Masland. AtlasMasland is located at 716 Bill Myles Drive, Saraland, AL,
           36571. The carpet evaluated in this study has a weighted average face fiber weight of 31.8 oz/square yard (sy) (1.08
           kg/m2) and a total weight of 69.8 oz/sy (2.37 kg/m2). All product characteristics fall within the ranges listed in Table 1.
           The face fiber is composed of nylon 6,6, and it is tufted on a primary backing made from polypropylene (PP). There is a
           secondary backing sheet of PP, and back coatings are styrene butadiene latex (SBL) with calcium carbonate as filler.
name: Broadloom Carpet

description:
Modular Carpets are composed of multiple layers. Components include the face yarn, primary
synthetic backing, latex compound, and a fi berglass layer inserted between two thermoplastic layers (secondary backing). Modular Carpets exist in different colors, designs and with four different yarn types: nylon 6, recycled nylon 6, polypropylene, and polyester. Carpet density varies between 3.5 kg/m2 and 4.4 kg/m2. For carpets made with nylon 6 yarn or polypropylene yarn, there is variation in the density of the yarn. The weighted average profi le for nylon 6 and polypropylene yarn carpets is calculated based on 2016 annual production data (on mass basis) of the 28 nylon 6 Modular Carpets and 14 polypropylene Modular Carpets, respectively. Product descriptions can be found at https://
www.venturecarpets.com/en/carpet-tiles/.
name: Modular Carpets with Polypropylene yarn

description:
The product is a commerical carpet tile with EcoSolution Q100™ face fiber on the EcoWorx® backing system. EcoSolution
Q100™ face fiber is nylon 6 with 100% pre-consumer recycled content. The EcoWorx® backing system consists of polyolefin
compound, recycled materials, and a fiberglass reinforcement layer. The face fiber is tufted into a primary backing that may
contain recycled content, latex is added to hold in the fiber, and the EcoWorx® backing system is applied.
